# Gauntlet starter pack - generated by tools_gen_pack.py
# Edit this file (or drop your own .pack next to it) to add challenges.
# Keys: PACK AUTHOR DESC | CHALLENGE CATEGORY POINTS DIFFICULTY
#       PROMPT DATA HINT FLAG/ANSWER EXACT

PACK Gauntlet Starter
AUTHOR at0m-b0mb
DESC A tour of every category: cipher, RFID and IR. Start here.

CHALLENGE Welcome to the Gauntlet
CATEGORY misc
POINTS 50
DIFFICULTY easy
PROMPT Every run starts with a warmup. Your flag is the word GAUNTLET, all lowercase. Press OK and type it.
HINT It is literally in the prompt.
FLAG gauntlet

CHALLENGE Caesar's Salad
CATEGORY cipher
POINTS 100
DIFFICULTY easy
PROMPT A classic shift cipher hides a name. Decode it and submit ONLY the name.
DATA WKH NHB LV EUXWXV
HINT Every letter moved by 3. Open the Toolkit and dial ROT.
ANSWER c00531e8

CHALLENGE Onion Router
CATEGORY cipher
POINTS 100
DIFFICULTY easy
PROMPT ROT-13 is its own inverse. What is the password? Submit just the word.
DATA GUR CNFFJBEQ VF BAVBA
HINT ROT-13. The Toolkit opens on it.
ANSWER 721c6d16

CHALLENGE Base of Operations
CATEGORY cipher
POINTS 100
DIFFICULTY easy
PROMPT This string ends in '='. Decode it.
DATA Z2gwc3RfcHJvdG9jb2w=
HINT That padding means Base64.
ANSWER 938edf82

CHALLENGE Hex Marks the Spot
CATEGORY cipher
POINTS 100
DIFFICULTY easy
PROMPT Two hex digits per character. Turn it into text.
DATA 63 31 70 68 33 72
HINT Use the Hex -> Text tool.
ANSWER 8d55e544

CHALLENGE Ones and Zeroes
CATEGORY cipher
POINTS 100
DIFFICULTY medium
PROMPT Eight bits per character. Decode the word.
DATA 01010000 01010111 01001110 01000101 01000100
HINT Binary -> Text. Each group is one letter.
ANSWER 67acbce3

CHALLENGE Can You Hear Me
CATEGORY cipher
POINTS 120
DIFFICULTY medium
PROMPT Dots, dashes and a slash for the space. Decode it.
DATA ..-. .-.. .. .--. .--. . .-. / --.. . .-. ---
HINT Morse. '/' separates words.
ANSWER cb0021b1

CHALLENGE Through the Looking Glass
CATEGORY cipher
POINTS 120
DIFFICULTY medium
PROMPT The alphabet is mirrored: A<->Z, B<->Y. Decode the word.
DATA draziw
HINT That is Atbash.
ANSWER fc030f0a

CHALLENGE Badge Dump
CATEGORY rfid
POINTS 150
DIFFICULTY easy
PROMPT A 13.56 MHz card's data block spells a word in hex. Read it back.
DATA 6b 65 79 63 61 72 64
HINT Hex -> Text again. RFID blocks are just bytes.
ANSWER 800b56e2

CHALLENGE Wiegand Unwrapped
CATEGORY rfid
POINTS 200
DIFFICULTY hard
PROMPT A 26-bit Wiegand read. Ignore the first and last (parity) bits. The next 8 bits are the facility code, then 16 bits are the card ID. Give the facility code in DECIMAL.
DATA 0 00101010 0000010100111001 0
HINT 00101010 in binary is the number you want.
ANSWER 87e38583

CHALLENGE Hidden Remote
CATEGORY ir
POINTS 150
DIFFICULTY easy
PROMPT An IR remote's secret label was captured as hex. Decode it.
DATA 70 6f 77 65 72
HINT Hex -> Text. It is a button name.
ANSWER f54f2346

CHALLENGE NEC Frame
CATEGORY ir
POINTS 200
DIFFICULTY medium
PROMPT A captured NEC infrared frame carries Address 0x00 and Command 0x45. Give the command byte in DECIMAL.
DATA Protocol NEC   Addr 0x00   Cmd 0x45
HINT 0x45 is 69 in decimal.
ANSWER 0ce8d410

